Perfect! Now I can see the issue clearly. The problem is that the `JsonGeneratorImpl` class overrides the `enable(Feature f)` method to handle `QUOTE_FIELD_NAMES`, but it does NOT override the `disable(Feature f)` method. This means when `QUOTE_FIELD_NAMES` is disabled, the `_cfgUnqNames` field is not updated properly.

The `enable` method correctly updates `_cfgUnqNames`:
```java
@Override
public JsonGenerator enable(Feature f) {
    super.enable(f);
    if (f == Feature.QUOTE_FIELD_NAMES) {
        _cfgUnqNames = false;
    }
    return this;
}
```

But there's no corresponding override for `disable`, so when `gen.disable(JsonGenerator.Feature.QUOTE_FIELD_NAMES)` is called, `_cfgUnqNames` remains unchanged.

The fix is to add the missing `disable` method override:

